citation.case_name: Murray Whitfield Coulter and George Prothro Coulter v. Garland Anthony, Fay Furlow, James Abbott

html:
358 U.S. 73

79 S.Ct. 153

3 L.Ed.2d 118

Murray Whitfield COULTER and George Prothro Coulter, appellants,
v.
Garland ANTHONY, Fay Furlow, James Abbott, et al.

No. 291.

Supreme Court of the United States

November 17, 1958

Mr. U. A. Gentry, for appellants.

Mr. J. E. Gaughan, for appellees.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
